<LEADPARA>  Pity the rich. The recession's been tough on them.;   In releasing its annual
list of the 400 wealthiest Americans, Forbes magazine -- a self-described
'capitalist tool' -- reported that since 1989, their net worth "has stagnated
. . . not even keeping pace with inflation."  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Front  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  KLUGE STILL RICHEST MAN IN U.S.  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  See also related article on page 8A of this section.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Nevertheless, the lowliest entry still posted a net worth of $275 million.
At the top was entertainment mogul John Werner Kluge with a fortune estimated
at $5.9 billion.;   Nearly three dozen Bay Area moguls are included, led by
electronics king David Packard.;   Also on the list, boasting the least
prestigious address: financier Michael Robert Milken -- of the Pleasanton
federal correctional center.  </TEXT>
